cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SOC

The paper discusses the use of social networks and social bookmarks for communicating research, which falls under the sub-categories of digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The focus on measuring the impact of scholarly publications also relates to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The mention of the San Francisco Declaration on Research Assessment and the need for proper safeguards and validations suggests a connection to the sub-categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and social and economic systems (cs.SOC).
